The paper deals with automatic radiology report generation using deep learning techniques, which is a natural language processing task (cs.CL). The focus is on radiology images, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The paper proposes the use of a pre-constructed graph embedding module, which involves learning representations of entities and their relationships, indicating a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a new evaluation metric, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
